Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.79,0:00:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A racing second hand,\Na shooting comet,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.66,0:00:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a pop-up doll,\Nand broken ceramic!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.87,0:00:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mystery-solving logic is helpful\Nagainst people's dry hearts!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.02,0:00:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji Hattori looks poised to discover\NConan's real identity today!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.28,0:00:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the\Nsingle truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.17,0:00:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there's no\Noutwitting his logic!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.63,0:00:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.29,0:01:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old man, Ran, and I went\Non a trip for Sherlock Holmes fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.47,0:02:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the car of Kanaya-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this trip's director and\Nowner of the Mycroft Lodge,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.81,0:02:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fell over a cliff and exploded!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.15,0:02:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, having been\Nisolated from the outside world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.99,0:02:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we shut ourselves in the lodge\Nto prevent any further casualties,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.03,0:02:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Ayako-{\i1}san{\i0}, who claimed\Nto know the identity of the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.37,0:02:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,died in an explosion in the garage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.33,0:02:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the owner responsible?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.46,0:02:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or was it one of the five other guests
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.67,0:02:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,excluding us three and Heiji Hattori?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.84,0:02:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly, Fujisawa-{\i1}san {\i0}was\Nattacked by someone with an ice pick!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.76,0:02:51.60,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Holmes Freak Murder Case (Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.35,0:02:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Holmes Freak Murder Case (Part 2).
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.52,0:02:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who would do such a thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He faked his death\Nduring the first incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.99,0:03:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,hid somewhere inside this lodge,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.36,0:03:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,burned Ayako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}to death in the garage,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.78,0:03:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then attacked Fujisawa-{\i1}san\N{\i0}with an ice pick
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.95,0:03:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and escaped out that window!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.96,0:03:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! Why would\Nthe owner want to kill me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I even helped him\Nwith the book he published!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.84,0:03:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Book?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.34,0:03:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Holmes book he published\Nlast year with his own money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.72,0:03:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe the title was\N"The Disparagement of Irene Adler."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.51,0:03:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irene Adler?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.31,0:03:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, Ran!\NWe're going after the owner!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.89,0:03:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.10,0:03:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about it.\NThere's no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.11,0:03:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd never find the\Nkiller by looking out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.90,0:03:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a closer look at this chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.11,0:03:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See how it's unnaturally\Nplaced at the narrow end?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's proof that the\Nkiller quickly pushed it under
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.12,0:03:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after breaking the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.58,0:03:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right! There are\Npieces of glass stuck in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer must have used this chair!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.09,0:03:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that only proves\Nthe killer used the chair to--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! Who would\Nbother putting a chair back
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after smashing a\Nwindow to escape through it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.55,0:04:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer probably\Nheld the chair with bare hands
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.22,0:04:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when they broke the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.10,0:04:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was too dark to\Nremove the fingerprints,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the killer put the\Nchair back under the table--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.06,0:04:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we wouldn't notice and so\Nthey could wipe the fingerprints off
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.49,0:04:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when no one was looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.15,0:04:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the lights came back on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, we were the\Nonly ones in the room then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.95,0:04:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.58,0:04:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now do you see\Nthat the owner didn't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.16,0:04:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that the killer\Nis in this very room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.80,0:04:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maid. You said a fuse had blown
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.30,0:04:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the lights went out, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.84,0:04:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! When I tried to\Nplug in the coffee maker,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.81,0:04:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it suddenly sparked!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.73,0:04:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was this outlet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.52,0:04:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a thin wire\Nwrapped around the plug
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.73,0:05:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that it would cause a\Nshort if someone were to plug it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.36,0:05:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But where did\Nthe killer get this wire?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.16,0:05:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it was this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.82,0:05:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wire attached to\Nthe top of this coffee pack!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.83,0:05:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The width and length\Ndo match perfectly...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.87,0:05:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who opened the packs?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawatsu-{\i1}san{\i0} and Togano-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.21,0:05:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.30,0:05:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the killer, Kawatsu-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.01,0:05:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were three other people\Nin the kitchen besides me--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.35,0:05:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All three of those people\Nhave alibis for the first incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.07,0:05:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You most likely took a wire off\Na pack when no one was looking,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.40,0:05:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wrapped it around the plug,\Nand then returned to the living room
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.91,0:05:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to wait for the lights to go out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:05:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, in the darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you attacked Fujisawa-{\i1}san\N{\i0}with an ice pick
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.41,0:05:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you carried in\Nhere with some ice--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,using the flame from\Nhis lighter to find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.88,0:06:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, some unexpected\Nobstacles caused you to fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.42,0:06:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.72,0:06:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but something's not quite right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.68,0:06:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.85,0:06:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third incident in which\NFujisawa-{\i1}san {\i0}was attacked
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.31,0:06:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is different than the first two
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.52,0:06:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in that the culprit plainly\Nleft evidence behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps this third incident\Nwasn't part of the killer's plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.45,0:06:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.07,0:06:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm just a kid,\Nso what would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't pay any attention to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He just loves to play detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.09,0:06:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.67,0:06:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something really\Nstrange about this kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.17,0:06:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't playing detective!\NHe's really analyzing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His voice and body are different,\Nbut he's almost just like Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:06:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.23,0:07:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! When Kudo showed\Nup during that previous incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.48,0:07:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that kid disappeared somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then when Kudo disappeared,\Nhe just popped up again...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.78,0:07:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could he really be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.75,0:07:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it strange, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Kawatsu-{\i1}san {\i0}really is the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how did he set the garage on\Nfire during the second incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And during the first incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.67,0:07:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the owner's car sped up\Nbefore it went over the cliff!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.60,0:07:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.97,0:07:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.77,0:07:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got almost all of\Nthe second incident solved,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.85,0:07:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the first incident\Nmakes no sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? You know how they set\Nthe garage on fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.69,0:07:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.15,0:07:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, what I don't\Nunderstand about the first incident
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the following four points.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.40,0:07:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why we didn't see the\Nowner for almost an entire day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.91,0:07:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the car suddenly sped up...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:08:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The odd sound coming\Nfrom inside the car
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.83,0:08:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the blanket on the dashboard...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.50,0:08:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then one more mystery\Nappeared when we came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.46,0:08:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The owner was holding\Nthe steering wheel tightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.17,0:08:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The car was on a bumpy road,\Nbut his body never slumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.01,0:08:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means by the time\Nhe was placed in the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was long dead\Nand rigor mortis had set in!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rigor mortis?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A body usually begins to stiffen\Nthirty minutes to two hours after death,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.94,0:08:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and nine to twelve hours later,\Nthe body becomes completely stiff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.32,0:08:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty hours after that,\Nunder the best circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.07,0:08:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the body loosens up again and\Napproximately seventy hours later
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.66,0:08:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we assume the\Nowner was completely stiff
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when he was placed\Nin the car at 3:30 a.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.00,0:08:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then he was killed between\N3:30 and 5:30 p.m. the previous day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.26,0:08:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,\Nsometime before dinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.88,0:08:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but what I don't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.30,0:09:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is why they had to\Nput him in the car so early...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.72,0:09:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe to make\Nit look like a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.43,0:09:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is that they\Nkilled the owner before dinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.56,0:09:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,put him in the car, had him\Nsit with his hands on the wheel,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.57,0:09:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,waited for him to stiffen,\Nthen went to the garage after dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.74,0:09:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and sent the car on its way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.86,0:09:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.24,0:09:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer was one of\Nyou who left after dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did the car speed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.12,0:09:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dead person couldn't\Npossibly have done that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.71,0:09:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dead person?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.04,0:09:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could the killer's trick be--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.38,0:09:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then only that\Nperson could've done it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.21,0:09:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's still no proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.13,0:09:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She did say that Ayako-{\i1}san {\i0}was\Nloitering in the hall in the afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.85,0:09:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she had actually seen\Nsomething in that person's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.10,0:09:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.44,0:09:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.44,0:09:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the killer's identity!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.44,0:09:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the killer is you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.95,0:09:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortuneteller Maria Toda-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.45,0:10:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg your pardon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.99,0:10:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have used hypnosis\Nto make the owner drive the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.41,0:10:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.67,0:10:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait to use\Na sleeping dart on him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.13,0:10:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's all over if he catches\Nme during my explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.13,0:10:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say! What would\Nhappen to the rigor mortis
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.80,0:10:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if the temperature went up?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.80,0:10:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would it start sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.97,0:10:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then you\Nknow who did it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.72,0:10:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't the slightest idea.\NI'm pretty dumb, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.52,0:10:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He knows all right, he's just\Ntrying to make me explain it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.94,0:10:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, in that case!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.28,0:10:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just be going\Nto the bathroom now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.49,0:10:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Then I will, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.03,0:10:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where'd he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.12,0:10:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you get serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.87,0:10:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a fortuneteller, not a magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough of this farce, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.34,0:10:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.67,0:10:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just figured out\Nwho the killer is, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.84,0:11:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.34,0:11:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.43,0:11:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person behind all three\Nincidents at this lodge... was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.94,0:11:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.69,0:11:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person behind all\Nthree incidents at this lodge...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.99,0:11:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.82,0:11:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.53,0:11:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man in a cold sweat behind you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.62,0:11:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you, Togano-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.38,0:11:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.67,0:11:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was here in the living room\Nhours before the car even took off!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.84,0:11:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when Ayako was killed,\NI was with everyone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.56,0:11:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right, you moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man! I hope he didn't wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.52,0:11:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you mock me with\Nyour fancy Kansai dialect!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.19,0:12:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, you were with us\Ntoo when the car started moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.95,0:12:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could Togano-{\i1}san\N{\i0}possibly have started the car?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, it certainly\Nappears impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.87,0:12:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he were to\Nutilize the rigor mortis
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.41,0:12:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a certain function of the car,\Nit would become possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.59,0:12:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The trick goes like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.25,0:12:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit killed the owner\Nalmost exactly one day ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.92,0:12:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sat him in the car seat,\Nand stuck his foot on the brake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.43,0:12:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rigor mortis would\Noccur half a day later,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.64,0:12:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the brakes would have\Nkept the car motionless
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.31,0:12:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even if the engine\Nwas running and in drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.94,0:12:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before dinner last night,\Nthe killer opened the garage
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.27,0:12:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then waited in the living room\Nfor the foot on the brake to loosen up
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.95,0:12:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and cause the\Ncar to start moving...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.74,0:12:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.28,0:12:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rigor mortis doesn't go away
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.53,0:12:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until at least forty hours after death!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.25,0:12:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You even said so yourself-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.71,0:12:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if the outside\Ntemperature increases?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.04,0:13:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the temperature around the body\Nwas about 95 degrees Fahrenheit,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the rigor mortis and rate of\Nloosening up would speed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.05,0:13:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it would start to go away after\Nonly twenty-four to thirty hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.72,0:13:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was after 10:00 p.m. two nights\Nago that the owner disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.98,0:13:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had been\Nkilled shortly afterward...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.64,0:13:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The car started moving approximately\Ntwenty-nine hours later
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--before 3:30 this morning--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.11,0:13:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which was just\Nabout the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.90,0:13:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hissing sound\Nwe heard inside the car
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.11,0:13:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't the air conditioner--\Nit was the heater!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.28,0:13:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had it been the AC,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.78,0:13:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,water drops would have\Nfallen by the front tires.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.41,0:13:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you were\Nchecking around the tire tracks?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.50,0:13:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.33,0:13:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, there were\Nno water marks to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.38,0:13:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that trick would\Nbe easy to see through
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.51,0:13:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by checking the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.05,0:13:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the killer sent\Nthe owner over the cliff in the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.93,0:13:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To make the body unrecoverable
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.77,0:13:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we couldn't check\Nthe state of rigor mortis!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.98,0:13:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why did the car speed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.31,0:14:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was probably because his\Nfoot slipped off the brake pedal
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.19,0:14:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the car bumped around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.36,0:14:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the blanket on the dashboard
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.49,0:14:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was there to conceal\Nthe heater indicator
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.99,0:14:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from people\Nwho got near the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.12,0:14:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.62,0:14:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So by witnessing the car\Nwith someone else in the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.00,0:14:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...they would\Nhave an airtight alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.17,0:14:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the reason Togano-{\i1}san {\i0}kept\NAyako-{\i1}san {\i0}in the living room
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.89,0:14:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was because he wanted someone\Nwho would witness the car with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.10,0:14:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.77,0:14:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the only person who\Ncould have done such a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.85,0:14:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was Togano-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.48,0:14:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.73,0:14:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your theory almost sounds\Nlike it's straight out of a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.74,0:14:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too bad you have\Nno evidence to prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.20,0:14:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And as I've said before,\Nwhen the fire erupted in the garage,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.04,0:15:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in here with everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.75,0:15:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how you look at it,\Nthere's no way
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.50,0:15:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could have set the fire exactly\Nwhen Ayako happened to go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but it would\Nstill be easy enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.51,0:15:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you had to do was tell her
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the first-edition Holmes book\Nwas hidden beneath the back seat
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the car in the garage!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.98,0:15:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first-edition book?\NWhat's that have to do with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.86,0:15:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.23,0:15:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, the car in the\Ngarage was drained of its gasoline
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and its battery removed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.65,0:15:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted to look for the book,\Nbut with the car lights unusable
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the back seat would\Nhave been pitch black.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.12,0:15:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.79,0:15:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were pitch dark, I'd have\Nto use a lighter or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.92,0:15:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! A lighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.29,0:15:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako-{\i1}san {\i0}used a\Nlighter to look for the book!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.97,0:15:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The flame ignited the gasoline\Nthat had leaked from the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.68,0:15:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she was the\None who started the fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.47,0:16:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she was an important\Nwitness from the first incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.02,0:16:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were four\Nother witnesses besides her!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.98,0:16:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no\Nneed to keep her alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.78,0:16:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't Ayako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}and Togano-{\i1}san {\i0}lovers?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.95,0:16:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.45,0:16:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because she figured\Nout his rigor mortis trick
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and found evidence that\Nhe was the one responsible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.83,0:16:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You all remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.17,0:16:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako-{\i1}san {\i0}declared\Nshe knew who the killer was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hearing that, \NTogano-{\i1}san {\i0}grew flustered
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.88,0:16:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and pretended to\Nfollow her to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.38,0:16:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He then told her\Nabout the first-edition book
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.39,0:16:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and lured her into\Nthe trap in the garage!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.68,0:16:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.22,0:16:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Togano-{\i1}san {\i0}was\Nthe only one alone with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.56,0:16:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why she changed her\Nattitude after leaving the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.56,0:16:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he certainly was clever\Nto come up with that garage trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.98,0:16:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. That trap had been prepared\Nin advance for a certain person...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.99,0:16:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer lucked out because\NAyako-{\i1}san {\i0}had a lighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.78,0:17:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just as that other\Nperson would have had!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.00,0:17:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The trap in the garage\Nwas really meant to kill Fujisawa-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.46,0:17:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.05,0:17:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That card that\Nwas stuck in your door...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.84,0:17:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer intended to lure\Nyou into the garage and murder you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But things didn't go according to plan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.73,0:17:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the garage trap\Nwound up killing Ayako-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He quickly devised\Na plan to cause a blackout
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.73,0:17:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by fiddling with the outlet
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.48,0:17:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then attacked\NFujisawa-{\i1}san {\i0}with an ice pick!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.48,0:17:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's why\Nthere was so much evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.65,0:17:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after the third incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.91,0:17:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Togano-{\i1}san {\i0}was in\Nthe kitchen at the time--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.49,0:17:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he could've very\Neasily fiddled with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.70,0:17:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the only person
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.91,0:17:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who could've pulled\Noff all three incidents...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.25,0:17:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was Togano-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.88,0:17:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then show us your proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.22,0:17:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to make such accusations,\Nthen surely you have proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.22,0:18:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You mean you didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.47,0:18:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako-{\i1}san {\i0}saw a certain\Nsomething in your room
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,yesterday afternoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.27,0:18:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter what she saw!\NShe can't talk now--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.56,0:18:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Question ♪1.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.86,0:18:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Which hand does\NHolmes write with?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.65,0:18:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Question ♪2.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.78,0:18:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"What is the name\Nof Dr. Watson's wife?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.36,0:18:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.28,0:18:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my. Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.29,0:18:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you take the Holmes Cult\NTest of 1000 Questions too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.29,0:18:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Question ♪241.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.50,0:18:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"What did Holmes' letter\Nwritten in the 'Dancing Men' code
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,say to the killer?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.55,0:18:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I remember\Nthat question very well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.01,0:18:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is,\N"Come here at once!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.81,0:18:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That question wasn't on the test...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.81,0:18:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was only that one question\Nabout "The Dancing Men"!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Write down the entire 'Dancing\NMen' code as it appeared!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.69,0:18:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.82,0:18:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That question was so hard it\Nwould be impossible to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.36,0:19:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a little strange\Nthat you don't remember it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.07,0:19:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.03,0:19:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason Ayako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}went to your room
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.33,0:19:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was to copy your test answers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.00,0:19:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you weren't in your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.33,0:19:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had probably gone to the garage
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.17,0:19:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to check the state of\Nthe owner's rigor mortis!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.59,0:19:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what Ayako-{\i1}san {\i0}saw was--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.68,0:19:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. A completely blank test\Nwith no answers written at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.72,0:19:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason he\Ndidn't write anything down
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.31,0:19:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was because\Nthere would be no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.19,0:19:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.02,0:19:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you knew that the owner\Nwouldn't be grading the tests
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.36,0:19:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because he was no longer alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.90,0:19:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to claim\Nthis is all nonsense,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.70,0:19:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then would you kindly\Nshow us your test?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.20,0:19:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.29,0:19:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.71,0:19:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.79,0:19:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speak up! Why did you\Nwant me and the owner dead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:19:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Disparagement of Irene Adler."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.88,0:20:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His motive was most likely\Nthe book you helped the owner write.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.47,0:20:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.89,0:20:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irene? The actress who outwitted\NHolmes in one of the stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.73,0:20:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But the owner's\Nbook was mostly about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.86,0:20:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes' failure as a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.19,0:20:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.19,0:20:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Togano-{\i1}san {\i0}felt that \Nthe book insulted Holmes, so he--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.36,0:20:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.11,0:20:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irene was the only\Nwoman Sherlock admired.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.91,0:20:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't possibly see\Nsuch a woman ridiculing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't allow it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.50,0:20:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I absolutely couldn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.77,0:20:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was incredible, Hattori-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.60,0:20:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what I'd expect from\Nthe great western detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.56,0:20:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.69,0:20:57.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.23,0:21:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A case like this is\Nlike a walk in the park for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.57,0:21:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I made it through\Nthis without having my cover blown...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.24,0:21:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.74,0:21:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right here, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.75,0:21:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.54,0:21:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Kudo, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.13,0:21:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you\Ntalking about? I'm just a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.55,0:21:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your fake Kansai\Ndialect was pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.09,0:21:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! So this is the gizmo\Nyou used to imitate my voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.68,0:21:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw you using it\Nin the corner of my eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.31,0:21:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At what point?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.89,0:21:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It would become possible."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.31,0:21:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talk a little strangely,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.27,0:21:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but from your tone and the\Nway you set up your theories
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.44,0:21:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you're definitely Shinichi Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.19,0:21:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?\NLook at me! I'm just a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.90,0:21:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, have it your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.12,0:21:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, check this out!\NYou'll never guess!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.29,0:21:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.71,0:21:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.93,0:23:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So their drug shrunk you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.59,0:23:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and now you're living\Nwith your girlfriend
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.49,0:23:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to find out about\Ntheir organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.93,0:23:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not my girlfriend.\NShe's a pain in the ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.31,0:23:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two sure\Nare getting along well!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.00,0:23:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.30,0:23:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wanna hear what\NKudo once said about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.23,0:23:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said you're so annoying\Nhe can't stand you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.54,0:23:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Annoying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.30,0:23:56.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.63,0:23:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you get\Nfor putting me to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.51,0:24:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.63,0:24:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it was cut with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.81,0:24:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's trying to kill Hiroshi-kun
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.73,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and make it look like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.94,0:24:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.43,0:24:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The First Errand Murder!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.99,0:24:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.41,0:24:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Traffic Mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.69,0:24:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode sees the return of a popular series!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.55,0:24:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys play a huge role!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.68,0:24:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.77,0:24:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
